author: COMSOL
description:
This example demonstrates the modeling of a wind turbine blade made up of laminated composite material. The laminated composite is made up of carbon–epoxy, glass–vinylester, and PVC foam materials where foam is used as a core material. The composite laminate has large number of layers hence modeled using Equivalent Single Layer (ESL) theory.

First, a stress analysis of composite blade is performed in which blade is subjected to gravity, or centrifugal force, or both. The tip displacement, maximum stress values, and through-thickness stress distribution at a particular point on the blade is computed for various load cases. Second, a prestressed eigenfrequency analysis is performed for a range of operating speed and Campbell diagram depicting the variation of eigenfrequencies with rotation speed is generated.
